label.value: regulation of transcription involved in posterior neural plate formation

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter contributing to the formation of the posterior neural plate.

label.value: regulation of chromatin silencing at centromere

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of chromatin silencing at the centromere. Chromatin silencing at the centromere is the repression of transcription of centromeric DNA by altering the structure of chromatin.

label.value: positive regulation of chromatin silencing at centromere

definition.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of chromatin silencing at the centromere. Chromatin silencing at the centromere is the repression of transcription of centromeric DNA by altering the structure of chromatin.

label.value: regulation of chromatin silencing at silent mating-type cassette

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of chromatin silencing at silent mating-type cassette. Chromatin silencing at silent mating-type cassette is the repression of transcription at silent mating-type loci by altering the structure of chromatin.

label.value: positive regulation of chromatin silencing at silent mating-type cassette

definition.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate, or extent of chromatin silencing at silent mating-type cassette. Chromatin silencing at silent mating-type cassette is the repression of transcription at silent mating-type loci by altering the structure of chromatin.

label.value: translation regulator activity, nucleic acid binding

definition.value: Any selective and non-covalent interaction with a nucleic acid involved in the initiation, activation, perpetuation, repression or termination of polypeptide synthesis at the ribosome.

label.value: C-5 methylation on cytosine involved in chromatin silencing

definition.value: The covalent transfer of a methyl group to C-5 of cytosine in a DNA molecule that contributes to chromatin silencing.
The polysaccharide-based coating on the inner side of a lysosomal membrane that protects it from digestion by lysosomal enzymes.
The formation and maintenance of DNA loops that juxtapose the promoter and terminator regions of RNA polymerase II-transcribed genes and activate transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter.

label.value: regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter involved in somitogenesis

definition.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter that contributes to the formation of mesodermal clusters that are arranged segmentally along the anterior posterior axis of an embryo.

label.value: positive regulation of transcription involved in G2|M transition of mitotic cell cycle

definition.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription of target genes that are transcribed as part of the G2|M transition of the mitotic cell cycle.

A transcription regulation process in which the presence of one nitrogen source leads to the modulation of the frequency, rate, or extent of transcription of specific genes involved in the metabolism of other nitrogen sources.

A transcription regulation process in which the presence of one nitrogen source leads to an increase in the frequency, rate, or extent of transcription of specific genes involved in the metabolism of other nitrogen sources.

A transcription regulation process in which the presence of one nitrogen source leads to a decrease in the frequency, rate, or extent of transcription of specific genes involved in the metabolism of other nitrogen sources.
A ubiquitin-protein ligase activity that increases the rate or extent of the metaphase to anaphase transition of the mitotic cell cycle.
Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the repression of transcription by methylation of DNA, leading to the formation of heterochromatin.

label.value: positive regulation of methylation-dependent chromatin silencing

definition.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of the repression of transcription by methylation of DNA, leading to the formation of heterochromatin.

label.value: negative regulation of methylation-dependent chromatin silencing

definition.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of the repression of transcription by methylation of DNA, leading to the formation of heterochromatin.
Stops, prevents or reduces the activity of a polygalacturonase. Polygalacturonases catalyze the random hydrolysis of 1,4-alpha-D-galactosiduronic linkages in pectate and other galacturonans.
Stops, prevents, or reduces ornithine carbamoyltransferase activity, the catalysis of the reaction -  carbamoyl phosphate + L-ornithine -eq- phosphate + L-citrulline.

label.value: negative regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to iron ion starvation

definition.value: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter as a result of deprivation of iron ions.
A cell projection that is a short, rounded projection from a plant epidermal cell.
A plant cell papilla that is part of a leaf papilla cell.
A plant cell papilla that is part of a stigma papilla cell.
The region at growing end of the pollen tube cell, where polarized growth occurs.
A cell projection part that is a branch of a unicellular trichome.
A tubular cell projection that is part of a pollen tube cell and extends from a pollen grain.
Catalysis of the reaction -  malonate + ATP + coenzyme A -eq- malonyl-CoA + AMP + diphosphate.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a brassinosteroid.
Catalysis of the reaction -  7-hydroxymethyl chlorophyll a + 2 reduced ferredoxin + 2 H+ chlorophyll a + 2 oxidized ferredoxin + H2O.
Enables the directed movement of nicotinate into, out of or within a cell, or between cells.
Enables the directed movement of N-methylnicotinate into, out of or within a cell, or between cells.

label.value: negative regulation of transcription involved in G2|M transition of mitotic cell cycle

definition.value: Any process that inhibits or decreases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription of target genes that are transcribed as part of the G2|M transition of the mitotic cell cycle.
Enables the directed movement of thiamine pyrophosphate into, out of or within a cell, or between cells.
Catalysis of the reaction -  caffeoyl-CoA + a saturated primary alcohol -eq- an alkyl caffeate + CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + myristic acid + CoA -eq- AMP + diphosphate + myristoyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + palmitic acid + CoA -eq- AMP + diphosphate + palmitoyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + oleic acid + CoA -eq- AMP + diphosphate + oleoyl-CoA.
Catalyzes the reaction -  (3S)-2,3-epoxy-2,3-dihydrosqualene -eq- camelliol C.
Catalyzes the reaction -  a hydroxyacyl-CoA + 3 malonyl-CoA + 2 H+ -eq- a hydroxylated tetraketide alpha-pyrone + 3 CO2 + 4 coenzyme A .
Enables the directed movement of abscisic acid into, out of or within a cell, or between cells.

A conserved protein phosphatase type 2A complex which contains a protein phosphatase type 2A, a protein phosphatase regulatory subunit, a striatin, an FHA domain protein and other subunits (at least six proteins). In fission yeast this complex negatively regulate the septation initiation network at the spindle pole body.
Catalysis of the reaction -  an acyl-CoA + sn-glycerol 3-phosphate -eq- CoA + a 2-acyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate.
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  glucosinolate(out) + H+(out) -eq- glucosinolate(in) + H+(in).
Catalysis of the reaction -  IDP + H2O -eq- IMP + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  9,15,9'-tricis-zeta-carotene -eq- 9,9'-dicis-zeta-carotene.
Enables the transfer of a vitamin from one side of a membrane to the other.
Catalysis of the reaction -  phosphatidylglycerol + phosphatidylethanolamine -eq- cardiolipin + ethanolamine.

Enables the directed movement of a drug into, out of or within a cell, or between cells. A drug is any naturally occurring or synthetic substance, other than a nutrient, that, when administered or applied to an organism, affects the structure or functioning of the organism -  in particular, any such substance used in the diagnosis, prevention, or treatment of disease.

Catalysis of the transfer of a methyl group from S-adenosyl-L-methionine to the oxygen atom of a nucleoside residue in a small RNA molecule. Reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + small RNA -lt--eq--gt- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + small RNA containing a 3'-terminal 2'-O-methylnucleotide.
